text.__SUMMARY__: Styloptygma aciculina is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Distribution: This marine species occurs off New Caledonia
text.References: Peñas A. & Rolán E. (2016). Deep water Pyramidelloidea from the central and South Pacific. 3. The tribes Eulimellini and Syrnolini. Universidade de Santiago de Compostela. 304 pp.page(s): 280, figs 14E, 74D-H
